HEADWORD: cinema
<hw>cinema</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>the art of creating
motion pictures; <as>as, this story would be good <ex>cinema</ex></as>;
-- often used in the phrase <altname>the cinema</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> the film.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>a theater where motion pictures are shown.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> movie theater, movie theatre, movie house, picture
palace.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>same as <er>motion picture</er>.</def>
<mark>[Chiefly Brit.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

